name: The Dera By Square Soarrow

reviews.review_text:
A Must-Visit in Anjuna!*
I stumbled upon Dera Bar and Restaurant in Anjuna, and it's been my go-to spot ever since! This place has got it all - good vibes, great music, and adorable decor.

What I love most about Dera is that it stays open until early morning, making it the perfect spot to hang out with friends in Anjuna. The ambiance is lively and energetic, with fantastic music that you can vibe with and dance to all night long.

But what truly sets Dera apart is its OUT-OF-THE-WORLD food! I've tried a variety of dishes, and each one has been great.  And the best part? It's incredibly affordable!

The staff at Dera are super polite, hospitable, and always ready to help.

If you're in Anjuna, do NOT miss out on Dera Bar and Restaurant! It's a hidden gem that'll become your favorite spot in no time.
One good thing about the place is it is vegetarian. We went on a monsoon night. Had some pizza and coke float. It was good. The ambience was also simple and good.

Visited here the second time but everything has changed, worst pizza ever served, apparently they think everything taste good when you spread extra cheese on everything, very slow service even though there was nobody else at that moment.

description:
### Discovering The Dera By Square Soarrow: A Hidden Gem in Anjuna

With an impressive rating of **4.2** stars based on **1,020 reviews**, The Dera By Square Soarrow shines as one of Anjuna's must-visit dining spots. Nestled near the serene coastline, this vibrant establishment resonates with visitors through its strong emphasis on **music** (43 mentions), **starters** (10 mentions), and a selection of refreshing **beer** (9 mentions), making it a favored haunt for locals and tourists alike.

### Ambiance & Design

Upon entering The Dera, guests are immediately enveloped in a lively atmosphere characterized by colorful decor that feels both inviting and playful. The walls are adorned with charming artwork, and the cozy seating arrangements enhance the overall experience. The soft, ambient lighting sets the perfect mood for evening gatherings, while the rhythmic beats of a carefully curated playlist create an infectious energy that beckons diners to stay a little longer. From the lively reactions shared in reviews, it’s clear this restaurant is not just a place to eat but a vibrant social hub where memories are made, especially with friends on breezy nights along the beach.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The Dera prides itself on a diverse menu that caters well to both meat-lovers and vegetarians, with the latter being a notable highlight. Diners rave about the **pizzas** and assorted **starters**, though the opinions are mixed regarding the culinary experience. Many praise the affordability and delightful flavors of the dishes, with one enthusiastic patron declaring, “It’s OUT-OF-THIS-WORLD food!” However, not all guests have had the same positive experience, as evidenced by one review lamenting the quality of the pizza during a return visit, suggesting an inconsistency in their culinary execution. Additionally, diners can expect fairly generous portions and vibrant presentations that please both the palate and the eye.

### Customer Experience & Service

Service at The Dera generally garners praise for its warm, hospitable staff. Reviewers frequently mention the politeness and readiness of the team to assist, which enhances the overall dining experience. However, there are mixed opinions on service speed. While many visitors enjoy smooth and quick service, others have noted slow waits during busy times, stressing the importance of staff attentiveness. The Dera operates late into the early morning, accommodating those late-night food cravings, particularly favored by the younger crowd.

### Popularity & Reviews

The restaurant has built a solid reputation, evidenced by the multitude of reviews it has accrued on social media and review platforms. Many customers tout it as a hidden gem, which adds to its allure. Highlights of the positivity surrounding The Dera speak volumes, with descriptions such as “good vibes” and “adorable decor” echoing through multiple reviews. Yet, as with any bustling locale, it also sustains a few critiques, particularly regarding food consistency and wait times, suggesting that the management could benefit from fine-tuning operations.

### Utilizing Visual Content

Visuals shared by patrons offer a glimpse into both the ambiance and the culinary delights that await guests at The Dera. Photos showcase the colorful decor and lively atmosphere, making the restaurant seem both inviting and energetic. The images of the food tell their own story, revealing the tempting presentation of dishes that spark curiosity and desire—from fresh starters to the beloved pizzas, each plate is designed to delight.

In summary, **The Dera By Square Soarrow** is more than just a place to eat; it’s a vibrant experience that captures the essence of Anjuna. Whether you're drawn in by the **music**, craving a late-night snack, or longing for a relaxed meal by the beach, The Dera promises an enjoyable retreat that will keep you coming back. Don't miss out on this gem; it could very well become your new favorite hangout spot.
